    "content": "From \"Samch'ŏlli\" to \"Taedong'a\"\n\nOur magazine \"Samch'ŏlli\" (三千里), which was first published in April of Shōwa 4 (1929) and has continued publication through fourteen years (星霜), now, taking the opportunity of the historic great turning point in Asia, changes its title (題號) to \"Taedong'a\" (大東亞) effective from today [Note: Announcement dated May 1st, 1942, published in the March 1st, 1942 issue], and further renewing its contents, intends to strive vigorously towards the noble national policy (國策) of the state (邦家). We humbly request even more guidance and encouragement (指導鞭撻).\n<13>\n\nMay 1st, Shōwa 17 (1942)\nTaedong'a Company (大東亞社)\n\n**Summary**\n\nThis brief announcement details the renaming of the Korean magazine \"Samch'ŏlli\" (Three Thousand Ri, a common name for Korea) to \"Taedong'a\" (Great East Asia). The change, effective May 1, 1942, is explicitly justified by the \"historic great turning point in Asia\" (referring to the Pacific War) and a desire to \"strive vigorously towards the noble national policy of the state\" (aligning with Japan's Greater East Asia Co-Prosperity Sphere ideology). For historians, this text starkly illustrates the co-option and transformation of Korean media under late Japanese colonial rule, forced to directly promote imperial wartime objectives and ideology, even erasing traditional Korean symbolism (\"Samch'ŏlli\") in favor of Japanese imperial terms (\"Taedong'a\").\n\n**Named Entities**\n\n昭和\t쇼와\tShōwa\n아세아\t아세아\tAsea\n邦家\t방가\tPangga\n大東亞社\t대동아사\tTaedong'a-sa\n\n**Glossary**\n\n창간\t창간\tFirst publication/launch (of a periodical)\n星霜\t성상\tYears; time; annals (lit. stars and frost)\n오든\t오던\t(verb ending) which used to come/be; older spelling of 오던\n금일\t금일\tToday; the present day\n題號\t제호\tTitle (of a publication)\n改하옵고\t개하옵고\t(We) change (humble form); older orthography/form of 개하고\n일층\t일층\tFurther; even more; one layer\n쇄신\t쇄신\tRenewal; reform\n邦家\t방가\tThe state; the nation (here referring to the Japanese Empire)\n國策\t국책\tNational policy\n邁進코저\t매진코자\tIntending to strive vigorously towards; older form/spelling of 매진하고자\n指導鞭撻\t지도편달\tGuidance and encouragement (lit. guidance and whipping)\n주시옵소서\t주시옵소서\tPlease give (extremely humble imperative form)\n\n\n---------------------------\n\n\n잡지명\t대동아 제14권 제3호\n발행일\t1942년 03월 01일\n기사제목\t「三千里」를 「大東亞」로\n기사형태\t사고·편집후기\n\n「三千里」를 「大東亞」로\n昭和 4년 4월에 창간하여 이래 14개 星霜을 계속 발간하여 오든 본지 「三千里」는 금에 아세아의 역사적 대전환을 계기로 금일부터 題號를 「大東亞」로 改하옵고 내용을 일층 쇄신하여 邦家의 숭고한 國策에 邁進코저 하오니 더욱 많은 指導鞭撻을 주시옵소서.\n昭和 17년 5월 1일\n大東亞社\n＜13＞",
    "magazine": "大東亞 제14권 제3호",
    "date": "1942년 03월 01일",
    "title": "Changing \"Samcheolli\" to \"Greater East Asia\""
